@vipulved They used 2FA to auth me. And then also forcibly reset my password. This is eBay. 

The kicker is that they did the two factor auth with a code to my e-mail. So I passed that but then they reset my pw via e-mail.

If my email was compromised why reset my pw via e-mail??  🙄

@keithtobin25 No. It shows the case they aren’t equal to MS.

“Public cloud providers” is a broad category. It includes all kinds of orgs even if you just look at the very largest.

I doubt, for example, that Alibaba, is comparable to the largest USA banks in terms of security sophistication.

@keithtobin25 Sure. I don’t understand why you think that obviates my point.

You think governments and other large businesses aren’t active in the same way??

My point is that it’s not inherently about cloud. I’m not saying anything about MS’s capabilities.

@jason_farns It’s fine. We are sort of generally aligned in thinking. I’m just less cynical.

Also I doubt it’s going away. A far more interesting question is how it integrates into existing systems, what does it disrupt, and how does the landscape change.

It’s not disappearing.

@jason_farns I don’t know. That’s a little cynical. The people I know who believe that truly do believe it.

It’s just that it’s a pipe dream. Societal structures won’t allow it.

It doesn’t event have to do with government.

@rjhintz @dgourlay That’s the OTHER hype now man. You know the one the government wants to regulate because … it’s hype?

I am under no illusion that crypto has no bad actors but it’s certainly more “real” than the metaverse. Momentum is momentum.

The metaverse is just a pipedream.

