@rbowen @OpenStack 🤷‍♂️ I saw myself as a teller of truths. In the beginning that meant a cheerleader for @OpenStack. An optimist.

Later as cracks formed that looked like bad news it meant critiquing to try &amp;  fix it. Still an optimist. 

Now just a realist. Apparently that is hard to understand?🙄

@jmckenty @OpenStack I don’t hate it. I said it’s a failed open source project. Don’t put words in my mouth. 

Also, it wasn’t about an agenda, it was about respecting my employers who had skin in the game on it.

You will notice that I stopped advocating for it for a long time.

@InfoWorld @mjasay It's funny, I was talking about this 7 years ago in a different, but related context, which is OpenStack API compatibility with AWS.  I made it clear that just modeling the API wasn't enough:

https://t.co/s17THYdPcZ

APIs are just a window into a system, not the system itself.

@jamesurquhart Hard to say. The Warriors have always had an almost tick tock rhythm. Frequently a loss makes them bounce back hard. Long losing streaks haven’t been common.

But it probably depends on the Jazz. They have been serious closers. 

I will be happy if I get a good fight.

@CTOAdvisor Hosting is not cloud. Slapping an API on your hosting system is not cloud.

I bet if we looked at those customers impacted, they did not fully automate their systems on OVH.

It might be better to assess cloud by how it’s used rather than what services it nominally provides.

