@brunoborges Somehow that feels outside the scope of humanity’s trajectory. What’s that quote again?

“The candle that burns twice as bright shines for half as long.”

Hopefully I’m wrong. I’m actually in full support of slowing down.

@furrier The difference between classic big business (not hyperscalers) and startups:  fear of failure.  Everything else relates to that.

Big business culture punishes failures.  Startups reward failure.

That's basically it.

